lassical approach to compute the neutrino mass\nmixing matrix at leading order(LO), e.g., in the absence of $CP$ violation\ncorrection. We obtain $\\theta_{12}=31.7^\\circ, \\theta_{23}=45^\\circ$ and\n$\\theta_{13}=0^\\circ$(the golden ratio pattern), which is consistent with an\n$A_5$ flavor symmetry pattern. We further predict an exact mass ratio of the\nthree mass eigenstates of neutrinos with $m_1/m_3=m_2/m_3=3/\\sqrt{5}$ and an\neffective mass of neutrinoless double beta decay\n$m_{0\\nu\\beta\\beta}=m_1/\\sqrt{5}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 12 Aug 2013 08:11:37 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 21 Apr 2016 05:55:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-09-02"}
